			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>I am open to that, but my strong suspicion is that the gains to the publishers are only positive if the books are destroyed. This is especially the case since people could re-buy up the used books and then trade them back in for a Kindle version. In equilibrium, used books have to go for the same price as Kindle books, net of transaction and shipping costs.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

