			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Don&#8217;t those have to converge anyway if this is implemented? People who want to get an ebook version will buy a used book and take it in for trade instead (since currently ebooks almost always cost more than used physical books). So used book markets are going to quickly dry up and take the price up with them. </p>
<p>I have a strong intuition that scenarios where a physical resource is deliberately destroyed are optimal. If someone values having it, it feels like there should be a better solution. But maybe not in this case.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

